This paper discusses the implementation of hardware decoders for polar codes, which are a type of error-correcting code used in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses various decoding algorithms and their advantages, which could fall under the categories of embedded systems (cs.ET), computer architecture (cs.AR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and control systems (cs.SY).
